III. BRIEF DESCRPTION OF THE DRAWINGS


FIG. 1 illustrates a first embodiment of a spectrometer of the subject invention;


FIG. 2 illustrates a method of operation of a first embodiment of a spectrometer of the subject invention;


FIGS. 3(a) and 3(b) illustrate an embodiment of the subject invention in which the distance be slits is increased to avoid substantial overlap of the spectra of the various light sources;


FIGS. 3(c) and 3(d) illustrate an embodiment of the subject invention in which filtering avoids substantial overlap of the spectra of the various light sources;


FIG. 4 illustrates an implementation example of the photodiode array of FIG. 1; and


FIG. 5 illustrates a second embodiment of a spectrometer of the subject invention.
